Class JsonHttpClient

JSON HTTP Client.

Implementation is not thread-safe.

Upgrade warning: prior to version 1.10 there was a {@code builder} method in JsonHttpClient, this has been removed in version 1.10. The Builder can now be instantiated with Builder.Builder(HttpTransport, JsonFactory, String, String, HttpRequestInitializer).

@since 1.6 @author Ravi Mistry

Class JsonHttpClient.Builder, GenericUrl getBaseUrl()

Returns the base URL of the service, for example {@code "https://www.googleapis.com/tasks/v1/"}. Must be URL-encoded and must end with a "/". This is determined when the library is generated and normally should not be changed.

Use this method only if {@code baseUrl} is used instead of {@code rootUrl} and {@code servicePath}.

@deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.11) Use .getRootUrl and .getServicePath instead.

Class JsonHttpClient, InputStream executeAsInputStream(HttpMethod, GenericUrl, Object)

Builds and executes an HttpRequest and then returns the content input stream of HttpResponse. Subclasses may override if specific behavior is required.

Callers are responsible for closing the input stream after it is processed. Example usage: 


     InputStream is = client.executeAsInputStream();
     try {
       // Process input stream..
     } finally {
       is.close();
     }
@param method HTTP Method type @param url The complete URL of the service where requests should be sent @param body A POJO that can be serialized into JSON or {@code null} for none @return input stream of the response content @throws IOException if the request fails @since 1.8
Class JsonHttpClient, HttpResponse executeUnparsed(HttpMethod, GenericUrl, Object)

Builds and executes a HttpRequest. Subclasses may override if specific behavior is required, for example if a sequence of requests need to be built instead of a single request.

Callers are responsible for closingdisconnecting the response's content inputHTTP streamresponse by calling HttpResponse.ignoredisconnect. Example usage: 


     HttpResponse response = client.executeUnparsed(method, url, body);
     try {
       // process response..
     } finally {
       response.disconnect();
     }

Class JsonHttpParser

Parses HTTP JSON response content into an data class of key/value pairs.

Implementation is thread-safe.

Sample usage: 

 
  static void setParser(HttpRequest request) {
    request.addParser(new JsonHttpParser(new JacksonFactory()));
  }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv InbarInbar @deprecated (scheduled to be removed in 1.11) Use JsonObjectParser instead.
Class JsonHttpRequest, void download(OutputStream)

Sends the request to the server and writes the content input stream of HttpResponse into the given destination output stream.

This method closes the content of the HTTP response from HttpResponse.getContent().

@param outputStream destination output stream @throws IOException I/O exception @since 1.9
